node.text: My son, I’ve dreamt of you since I was a child. I’ve wanted nothing more than to be a mom my entire life, being told it would never be possible was a pain I lived with for more than half my life. Sometimes I look at you and still don’t believe it. You were sent here for me. You are my purpose. I am amazed and in awe of you and like every mother think you are the smartest two year old that ever lived. Even on my hardest days when I want to pull my hair out and scream I put you to sleep and miss you. Being a Mom is the hardest job in the entire world but I would take the sleepless nights, constant worry, and responsibility over and over again to feel this love. Thank you God 🤍🧿

node.text: 💉 Being in the industry I’ve realized that one of the most common things people confuse is what Botox actually does and where it can be used. Botox is the name brand of one of the most popular and well known Neuromodulators. Botox causes temporary paralysis of the muscle and in turn creates a smoother more relaxed look in areas such a the glabella (frown lines) and forehead. Botox can not “fill” out already defined wrinkles, But it can drastically soften the appearance of lines and wrinkles and overtime help diminish the look of already existing wrinkles. I often get asked when is the right age to begin, no such thing. If and when you are developing lines on your forehead or glabella in a resting position it is time!

To celebrate the upcoming National Botox Day on 11.18.20, we are giving away $2500 AND a year’s worth of Botox* for one lucky winner! 

It takes 30 seconds to enter:

✅ Follow @drchiubhps and @jessica___ 

✅ Tag 3 friends on this post @drchiubhps and tell us what you’ll do with the $2500

✅ Share this giveaway on your instastory 
 
Entry period runs from 11/12/2020 to 12PM PST on 11/18/2020. Qualified winner will be selected and announced at 7pm PST 11/18/20
*30 units of Botox every 3 months for 1 year.
 
‼️ALL ENTRANTS TO RECEIVE A SURPRISE GIFT‼️
 
Giveaway is not affiliated with Instagram. Dr. Chiu/BHPS and its affiliates reserve the right to deny medical treatment to those they do not deem fit. Medical assessment will be required prior to treatment. Botox cannot be redeemed as cash.
